Label: SUPT16H
Comment: DSIF is a heterodimer consisting of hSPT4 (human homolog of yeast Spt4- p14) and hSPT5 (human homolog of yeast Spt5-p160).  DSIF association with Pol II may be enabled by Spt5 binding to Pol II  creating a scaffold for NELF binding (Wada et al.,1998). Spt5 subunit of DSIF can be phosphorylated by P-TEFb.

Label: p-S2,S5-POLR2A
Comment: The C-terminal domain (CTD) of POLR2A contains about 52 repeats of the consensus heptad YSPTSPS. Serines-2 and 5 of the heptads are phosphorylated in RNA polymerase II initiating transcription of protein coding genes. The exact repeats that are phosphorylated are not known.
